      "ReadOnly": false
    },
    {
      "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
      "Text": "Data description: https://doi.org/10.26182/p0bd-k580.\n \nDisclaimer: This dataset is provided “as is” without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to its accuracy, completeness, or fitness for a particular purpose. The creators and contributors shall not be liable for any damages arising from its use.\n\nFor further inquiries or permission requests, please contact Dr Sheng Chen (sheng.chen@uwa.edu.au) and Rajneet Uppal (rajneet.uppal@dpird.nsw.gov.au).\n \nWhen citing this dataset, please use the following reference: Chen, S., Cowling, W.A., Siddique, K.H.M., 2023. Field trials for validation of canola heat tolerance under heat-prone environments (Cycle 1). https://doi.org/10.26182/p0bd-k580.\n\nWhen using the damage functions, please use the following reference for more information: Hu, P., He, D., Zheng, B., Whish, J., Kirkegaard, J., Bell, L., Leske, B., Chen, S., Uppal, R., Biddulph, B., Trethowan, R., Beletse, Y., Lilley, J., 2026. Event-based frost and heat damage functions improve yield predictions of APSIM canola and wheat: formulation, calibration, and evaluation. Agricultural and Forest Meteorology 386, 111239. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.agrformet.2026.111239",
      "Name": "Data Ownership Acknowledgement",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [],
      "Enabled": true,
      "ReadOnly": false
    },
